news.title: Sustainable green plan for urban areas soon: Gurugram development body
news.para: According to officials, although the GMDA Act, 2017, mandated that such a plan should be prepared “from time to time”, the district environment management plan was prepared and released by the state government, creating uncertainty about whether a separate plan was required for the GMDA areas.

news.title: Bengaluru: Brookfield Layout residents to crowdfund, plan & construct road by themselves
news.para: The proposal has received the green signal from the MLA of the area and the project is estimated to cost Rs 5.5 lakh. It will be crowdfunded and carried out by the resident welfare association of the area.

news.title: Mumbai: 223 high-rises get fire brigade notices for safety violations in two months
news.para: The notices were issued to these structures under the Maharashtra Fire Prevention and Life Safety Measures Act, 2006, for various deficiencies found in their fire-fighting systems, shows municipal data.

news.title: Government push for affordable housing scheme in Rajasthan
news.para: The decision was taken after the pace to construct affordable houses including economic weaker section (EWS) and lower income group (LIG) slowed down due to existing policies, which became a hindrance in achieving a target of 4,200 houses.

news.title: Pune civic body attaches 3,000 properties over tax default
news.para: “These property owners have been avoiding payment from a long time. Notices and warnings were sent. But they have not adhered to the guidelines. So, their properties have been attached,” Vilas Kanade, head of PMC’s property tax department, said.

news.title: Chennai: Ceebros Group set to acquire Adyar Gate hotel
news.para: Property developer Ceebros is finalising a redevelopment agreement with the Goyals, the family that owns the Adyar Gate Hotels Limited (AGHL).

news.title: Hyderabad: ED arrests Karvy chairman and MD in fraud case, seeks custody
news.para: ED said that the total loans taken by Karvy were estimated to be around 3,000 crore. Prima facie investigation revealed 1,096 crore was transferred by KSBL to its group company Karvy Realty (India) Ltd between 2016 and 2019.

news.title: Supertech says advance payment made to firm for Noida twin tower demolition
news.para: ​The details of the agreement have been shared with the New Okhla Industrial Development Authority (NOIDA) about the planned razing of the 40-storey superstructures that had come up in violation of building bye-laws in Sector 93A of the city, it said.

news.title: Suraksha group expects NCLT nod by March to acquire Jaypee Infratech
news.para: ​In the meantime, Suraksha ARC Managing Director and Chief Executive Officer Aalok Dave said the company is making preparations internally to start construction work on all stalled projects soon after the NCLT approval.

news.title: HDFC Capital raises $1.8-billion for affordable housing
news.para: The HDFC Capital Affordable Real Estate Fund-3 (H-CARE-3) is one the largest funds raised to invest in the residential real estate sector in India with investors committing in excess of USD 1.22 billion towards the first close.

news.title: Indore: 70 plot buyers of Satellite Hills to get possession
news.para: According to ADM Abhay Bedekar, a team of revenue officials on Friday laid a line of lime-powder as marking of plots in Satellite Hills to provide the possession to around 70-72 buyers on Monday.

news.title: Mumbai: Delays in okaying increased cost for Metro 3 line leave officials worried
news.para: The cost of the underground Metro-3 project has escalated by over Rs 10,000 crore to Rs 33,406 crore from the original estimate of Rs 23,136 crore in 2011.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Developers fail to repay Rs 1.64 crore loan, case filed
news.para: In his complaint Vishal Mir (27), a resident of Vinjol, has stated that he was working as business development manager with a home loan company.

news.title: Chandigarh: Installation of machines in C&D waste plant to start soon
news.para: ​After an intensive exercise over the past several months, the Chandigarh Municipal Corporation has received and cleared public objections received for the policy, which has been subsequently sent to the Chandigarh administration for final notification.

news.title: RLDA invites bids for development on railways land near Patna junction
news.para: The colony falls under the jurisdiction of Danapur division of East Central Railway (ECR). However, the entire site location is likely to be under the jurisdiction of Patna Municipal Corporation (PMC) as per the Patna Master Plan 2031.
